Yes, on Linux (Ubuntu) you can reset the GPU without a full reboot. A few options:

Check what's stressing it first — run this in terminal (screen 2):


nvidia-smi
That shows GPU usage, temperature, and which processes are using it.

Kill the process using the GPU — if something is hogging it, find the PID in the nvidia-smi output and kill it:


sudo kill -9 <PID>
Reset the GPU driver — this restarts the Nvidia driver without a full reboot:


sudo rmmod nvidia_uvm && sudo modprobe nvidia_uvm
Full driver reload (stronger reset, but requires no GUI running):


sudo systemctl stop display-manager
sudo rmmod nvidia
sudo modprobe nvidia
sudo systemctl start display-manager
Warning — option 4 will briefly kill your desktop.

